okay. i copied Natalie but y'know. kk Diet plan goes like this...[starts in summer holidays which is bout a week and a half away]

<u>Average Day of Food</u>
Breakfast - Shredded Wheat with low fat milk or Wholemeal toast with a tiny bit of butter. And once a week i can have some bacon with all the fattie bits taken off. And once a week i am allowed Scrambled eggs.

Snack - Fruit or Fruity yogurt [non fat]

Lunch - Non-fat Ham and Tomato Sandwich, or salad, or stirfry.

Snack - Fruit or Fruity yogurt [non fat]

Dinner - Pretty much everything apart from occasionally oven chips and no very fattie or oily things. lots of veg.

Snack - Fruit or Fruity yogurt [non fat]

Drinks - Diet Coke, Water or Fresh Orange Juice occasionly


<u>Excercise</u> [it might seem extreme but i <3 my trampoline]

Monday - Friday -- 1 1/2 hours on trampoline not including excercises [see below]

Sat and Sunday -- 2 hours on trampoline not including excercises - [see below]

<u>Trampoine Excercises</u>
20 star jumps
10 seat drops no hands into crossed legs
10 seat drops with hands into crossed legs
10 seat drops with hands into stretched legs
10 seat drops no hands into stretched legs
1 minute running [VERY hard on trampoline]
20 minutes boxing [ just jumping and punching to Brooke Valentine - Girlfight]


ALSO 30 sit ups and 20 press ups before breakfast.

My aim is to lose at least stone before the end of Summer Holidays so thats 3 pounds at least every week. But I think I can probably do it. I'll update every week especially to tell you how much I lost.
